post_text: Holdyn Gallagher earned the Good News Call on Friday. He was nominated for the call by our school counselor, Mrs. Konechne. Holdyn showed great kindness in our lunchroom by grabbing a dish cloth and helping Mrs. K. and Mrs. Knecht wipe lunch tables following elementary lunch. We asked him if he was on “table wiping duty", and he said, “No I’m just helping you wipe the tables.” He helped us wipe all tables; saving us a huge amount of work. He also helped the cooks with the silverware, and then he asked if he could assist with anything else. Thank you Holdyn for making the day easier and brighter for someone else.

The Platte Geddes Schools will NOT be hosting their Open House Event this year.

We have the following reminders for all students and parents:

*Make sure you are on Mr. Frederick and Mrs. Knecht's email groups so you are getting all back to school information. If you are a parent and you do not receive these emails, please call the elementary or high school to get on our email lists.

*For our grade level school supply lists please check your email, the Platte-Geddes School District Facebook page or go to our website at www.platte-geddes.k12.sd.us

*Our Return to Learn Plan will be emailed out to all parents and staff members this week. It will also be located on our website.

*Our buildings will be closed to all visitors and parents beginning on August 14, 2020. Only students and staff members will be allowed in the school. Please call the school if you have questions.

Attention Platte-Geddes 6th-12th Grade Students

*Platte-Geddes Junior High / High School is inviting students only to come into the building starting August 10th-13th. The building will be open from 9:00 a.m. until 3:00 p.m. each day for students to check out their computers (9th-12th students only), pick out their lockers, and complete/adjust schedules if necessary. Please keep in mind that we will be implementing social distancing practices during these times. We ask that students do not come in groups in order to help us keep everyone safe and healthy. If you have questions, please feel free to contact the high school office.

The P-G yearbook staff is having a presale for this year's yearbook (19-20), which will arrive sometime this coming fall. The presale will go through May 13 and the cost of a book is $55. All books must be ordered at this time--there will be no extras available after they arrive. If you'd like to purchase a yearbook, or if you are unsure if you have already purchased one, please contact Mrs. Larson (stacey.larson@k12.sd.us) or Mrs. Hubers in the HS office. All yearbooks will need to be paid for by May 20.
Checks can be made out to Platte-Geddes Schools.

post_text:
Press Release- For Immediate Release

At the request of Governor Noem, the remainder of the SDHSAA Class B Girls Basketball tournament is postponed. In addition, all SDHSAA state basketball tournaments for next weekend, along with the Visual Arts competition, are also postponed. The Student Council Convention, all Region music contests, and All-State Band scheduled for later this month are cancelled.

This is a difficult decision and comes amid constant conversation and information sharing between the SDHSAA, the Governor’s Office, and the Department of Health. We will evaluate the future of the postponed events in concert with those same entities. The safety of everyone involved is our foremost concern, followed by exploring all options to provide the student-athlete with the opportunity to finish their season.

We thank everyone for their patience and understanding in a very difficult time, and we apologize for any inconvenience that this may cause.

Dan Swartos, SDHSAA Executive Director

Congratulations to Bohde Kuiper, our Good News Call this week! Bohde was nominated for the Good News Call by Mr. Kemnitz. Also, thanks for your lovely smile all day every day!

He couldn't decide, so he called both Mom and Dad! ❤️❤️

post_text: We have another Good News Call this week going out to Miley Larson. Yesterday afternoon, on the recess playground, Miley went out of her way to assist Mrs. Knecht with a student who was running away instead of lining up. She caught up to him and immediately began encouraging the student to line up, in a kind manner. She offered to race the child and told him she could beat him to the line. Her kind encouragement convinced him to race her to line up and he went in perfectly. Miley is often seen helping kids line up and assisting the teachers with holding the hand of a student who isn't ready for recess to end. Thank you Miley for the help yesterday and for always being a kind and willing helper to our teachers.

Good News Call

Our Good New Call of the week goes out to Holdyn Gallagher. Holdyn has been assisting the cooks in the lunchroom, specifically Cindi with carrying the silverware tub. He has offered to help several times and Cindi has finally taken him up on the offer. When we offer to help someone, what we often times don’t even realize is that maybe, just maybe, they really, really do need our help. In this case, Cindi really did need the help and Holdyn willingly and happily assisted her. Thank you Holdyn for modeling the Panther Way expectation of Kindness by helping others. Your help meant more than you could possibly know to Cindi.

Thanks to every single parent for sending us such an AWESOME bunch of kiddos every day!!

Jennifer Knecht
Elementary Principal/SPED Director

She replied, He always gets out, I wanted him to run the bases this time.” There you go Panthers, an AWESOME example of kindness to others. Thank you Karina for modeling true KINDNESS and for putting others before yourself this Christmas Season!

post_text: The Platte-Geddes junior high and high school students and staff took on a fun challenge to spread kindness and giving. They all competed in a penny war collecting close to $500. post_text: Shay Petersen and Jameson Leader were nominated for the Good News Call of the Week by our wonderful custodian, Mike Anderson. Following the recent snowstorm, Mike had a great deal of shoveling to do around the elementary school building. However, after school on Monday, December 2, Jameson Leader and Shay Petersen each grabbed a shovel and helped Mike clear sidewalks, steps, and the elementary school walkways for over an hour. That’s right, these two boys gave up an hour of their after school free time to assist Mike with our snow clean up! Thank you to Shay and Jameson for noticing that Mike needed help, and for giving him your time; and thanks for showing such great KINDNESS and for modeling service to others! ❤️❤️ (And, how precious are these photos?....)

post_text: On World KINDNESS Day, yesterday, it was only appropriate that we had a KINDNESS Good News Call of the Week. Pictured above is Jace Vigoren calling his Mom, Tressa. Jace received the Good News Call for showing exceptional kindness to another small child at recess. She was asking for a push from a teacher, and before we arrived Jace began pushing her. He pushed her throughout the entire recess then and when recess was over, he picked up her stocking hat, on the ground, and gave it to her. Jace displays kind behaviors often and is an all-around super great kid! Thanks Jace for being such a KIND friend to others.

post_text:
Siena Settles was nominated for the good news call by our counselor, Mrs. Konechne, for showing the PantherWay expectation of KINDNESS. Mrs. K stated this regarding Siena, "EVERY time, and I mean EVERY time I see Siena in the hallway, usually before school, she shares a smile and a kind word" What a positive way to start your school day Siena! Siena is often heard giving other students and teachers compliments and is always willing to help others. We want you to know, your kindness towards others is noticed and appreciated Siena. Thank you for being a bright light in our day!

I would echo Mrs. K's kind words as I often observe Siena's kindness during our school day. On Thursday, after school, I observed Siena stop and zip the coat of a Kindergarten student as she was leaving the building. She often stops and tells me something kind when I meet her in the school hallways. Thank you Sienna for showing such sincere kindness to others. What a wonderful legacy of KINDNESS to leave in the elementary building.

post_text: Halloween Week at Platte Geddes Elementary ended with a "Good News Call" by 3rd Grader Cambree Foxley. Cambree is pictured below calling her mom, Jeana with the Good News. Cambree was nominated for the GNC by her long-term substitute teacher, Katy Duffy. Ms. Duffy stated, "Cambree has been so helpful to me during my time as Mrs. DuFrain's sub. She shows me where things are located and helps explain the normal daily routines so we can stay on track for when Mrs. DuFrain returns. She models to her classmates how to come into the classroom, work quietly during work time and listen during instruction, and how to be a respectful classmate to myself and her peers. Her positive attitude and willingness to help everyone make subbing joyful and easy." Thanks for being a great kid, Cambree!

The Platte-Geddes Cross Country teams had a beautiful day for the state meet in Huron and performed well. The Boys team finished in 3rd place. We had two state placers, Caden Tegethoff finished 21st and on the girls side, Kelly Sondgeroth finished 12th.

Members of the girls teams are Kelly Sondgeroth, Kally Millar, Addi Boltjes, Calli Slaba, and Katie Holter.

Members of the boys team are Caden Tegethoff, Nate Whalen, Collin Engebretson, Gavin Gustad and Trevor Rolland. (Photos courtesy of SDPB)

post_text: September 17th the juniors and seniors hit the road to Mitchell, SD to attend a college fair held at Dakota Wesleyan University's field house. There were numerous colleges and technical schools present along with military options. The students also attend a career fair hosted by Mitchell Technical Institute at the Davison County Fairgrounds. The career fair gave hands on experiences in many different career options for the students. The day concluded with tours of Mitchell Technical Institute or Dakota Wesleyan University before returning home for the day. Students had the opportunity to gather information on post secondary options to help guide their decision making for after high school.

post_text: The Platte-Geddes staff held a tailgate supper to provide funding to our neighboring Burke School District in an effort to provide financial support after a tornado had devastating effects to their school facilities. The Platte and Geddes communities stepped up to the plate along side the staff and were able to provide $3160 to the Burke School District. Community is what keeps us strong! Our P-G volleyball team presented a check to the Burke School District at last night's volleyball game.

Merrick took off his own hat and the camera that he was wearing and gave it to his friend saying, "Here you go, you can wear my stuff today for tourist day." Thank you Merrick, for modeling kindness and the Golden Rule by "Thinking of others as yourself." .....("In everything, do to others as you would have them do to you.")
We can sure learn a lot from the KINDNESS of our Kindergarten Models. Great Work Merrick!!

post_text:
Jimmy Foxley is our "Good News Call of the Week" to start our week on a positive note. Jimmy was nominated by his teacher, Mrs. Patzlaff, for assisting a Kindergarten child after school on Friday. The child was in the upper elementary hallway crying because he thought his sister had forgotten him at school. Jimmy took the child by his hand and showed him that his sister was still in her classroom and had not left him at school. Jimmy waited with the child by her classroom door until she came out and got her little brother. Thanks Jimmy for the kindness and for noticing that one of our little ones needed some help! What a kind and thoughtful gesture!

It looks like it's going to be a great week here at Platte Geddes Elementary! Jennifer

She comforted her by saying that "she too had been hit by balls and it does really hurt". She then hugged her and sat with her for awhile until the child stopped crying. Mr. Kemnitz stated...."This is a typical behavior I have seen often from Kori." Thanks for ALWAYS choosing KINDNESS, Kori! Great work!
